race.description: New Zealand Bloodstock - Karaka 100 Years Hcp
race.comment: IVY DIVA (8) appreciated the class drop when she came from near last on the turn for a dominant victory over 1300m at Narromine from the low gate. Deserves her chance at this level and can get the job done again. EMPUSA (4) bounced off her two good trials with an eye-catching fourth over 1250m at Newcastle. Returned good closing splits on that occasion and has genuine top-three claims. TOKYO STAR (3) is ready to peak fourth-up and has the speed to get across from the sticky barrier. Sat on the good tempo when a gritty fourth over 1400m at Canberra. Capable of playing a leading role. MELLENCAMP (11) has a good third-up record and proven at this track. Comes out of a strong rating contest after finishing seventh over 1300m at Scone. Keep safe.
